// cases.proto defines the account-scoped case persistence surface for the
// ZyINS Unified API. A "case" is an immutable, content-addressable
// snapshot of an underwriting evaluation (input + optional results +
// product list) that can be linked to from outside the API — the
// canonical agent-facing URL is `https://bestplanpro.com/?case=<hash>`.
//
// All routes are mounted under `zyins.isaapi.com/v1`. Every operation is
// account-scoped: the calling token determines `account_id`, every read
// filters by `account_id`, and there is no cross-account visibility at
// the query layer. Storage backs onto PostgreSQL (`store.CaseRepository`)
// with content-hash deduplication; large payloads spill to S3 with the
// row carrying an `s3_key` reference.
//
// Companion guides for integrators live in `api/guides/cases.md`. This
// file is the wire contract; the guides explain the dedup model, the
// readonly semantics, and the email helper.

